A '''criminal accusation''' is the process of declaring one's [[belief]] in another's [[Legal liability|liability]] for that other's [[Crime|criminal]] action(s). A criminal [[wikt:accusation|accusation]] may be informally made through a declaration made to the public at large (generally through news media) or by the filing of a formal accusation in a court of law by a person legally entitled to do so, generally on behalf of the state by a [[criminal]] [[prosecutor]].
