|short_title=Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act, 1960|legislature=[[Parliament of India]]|image=|imagealt=Scale of justice 2.svg|caption=|long_title=An Act to consolidate and amend the law relating to Prevention of Cruelty to Animals|territorial_extent=[[India]] (except [[Jammu and Kashmir]])|citation=http://www.envfor.nic.in/legis/awbi/awbi01.pdf|enacted_by=|date_enacted=|enacted_by2=|date_enacted2=|date_commenced=1 April 1974|bill=|bill_citation=|bill_date=|introduced_by=|1st_reading=|2nd_reading=|white_paper=|repeals=|related=[[Wildlife Protection Act, 1972]]|keywords=}}The '''Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act''' is an [[Act of Parliament|Act]] of the [[Parliament of India]] enacted in 1960 to prevent the infliction of unnecessary pain or suffering on animals and to amend the laws relating to the prevention of cruelty to animals.<ref>[http://moef.nic.in/modules/rules-and-regulations/animal-welfare/ ]{{dead link|date=August 2018}}</ref>  As per the provisions of the law the [[government of India]] formed the [[Animal Welfare Board of India]].<ref>[http://www.awbi.org/act.htm ]{{dead link|date=August 2018}}</ref>
The act however makes a provision under heading [Chapter VI, Heading 28] "Saving  as respects manner  of killing prescribed by religion" : Nothing  contained in this  Act  shall  render it an  offence  to kill any  animal in a  manner required by  the religion of any  community.
<ref>[http://www.moef.nic.in/sites/default/files/No.59.pdf]{{dead link|date=August 2018}}</ref>

